When Maxine Hong Kingston
went back to her house one day sev-
eral years ago, there was nothing
there. Her entire home and the ter-
rain’ around it was charred and
burned.

A devastating Oakland, Calif.,
fire in 1991 had not only destroyed
Kingston’s home, it had also con-
sumed the 156-page manuscript of

the book she_was working on, “The _

Fourth Book of Peace.”

As Kingston surveyed the area,
she imagined it must be what a war
zone looked like. .

“I came out into a changed
